<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,952,978]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing membrane with distinctive anterior dark brown band; aedeagus long; ejaculatory apodeme reaching base of gonocoxite, lateral ejaculatory process wide, projected at right angle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,269,1032,1058]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 8.0–9.0 mm. Wing length, 6.0–7.0 mm. General color brownish gray. Eyes brown, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle grayish brown, ocelli brownish. Gena and clypeus yellowish gray to brown, clypeus bare. Scape and pedicel brown, first flagellomere and arista darker; scape with setae, half the length of pedicel; pedicel approximately cubic; first flagellomere oval, as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1335,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,194,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[169,1417,194,1550]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 34 — Wing, 35 — Antenna, 36 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 37 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[1302,1335,1152,1178]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus long, slender (
<figureCitation box="[458,578,1192,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,194,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[169,1417,194,1550]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 34 — Wing, 35 — Antenna, 36 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 37 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[545,578,1192,1218]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proboscis dark brown, labella brownish yellow. Occiput gray, with silvery iridescent setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Thorax brownish gray, scutellum lighter than scutum. Halter bare, stem yellowish brown, brown knob. Coxae brownish gray, femora and tibiae yellowish, both with golden setae. Wing membrane with a distinctive anterior dark brown band (
<figureCitation box="[466,585,1352,1378]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,194,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[169,1417,194,1550]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 34 — Wing, 35 — Antenna, 36 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 37 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[552,585,1352,1378]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
); pterostigma pigmented, long, filling almost entirely cell; surroundings of crossveins hyaline; R 
<number box="[440,448,1408,1422]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[458,465,1408,1422]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C far from R 
<number box="[742,750,1408,1422]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
, not sinuous distally; R 
<number box="[1037,1045,1408,1422]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
forking with almost right angle, without short appendage; CuA 
<number box="[510,518,1451,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[596,604,1451,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
fusing far from margin; crossvein m-m not so far from origin of M 
<number box="[1392,1400,1451,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Abdomen homogeneously brown, with golden setae on tergites. Gonocoxite and gonostylus dark brown; gonocoxite wider than long; gonostylus elongated, slightly acuminate distally, long setae laterally, slender setae at medial portion; aedeagus long; ejaculatory apodeme long, reaching base of terminalia; gonocoxal apodeme relatively long, curved inwards; lateral ejaculatory process wide, projected at right angle (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 42" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,474,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[198,1390,474,2057]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 42. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 38 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 39 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 40 — Terminalia, ventral view, 41 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 42 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177240/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[151,184,1638,1664]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX deep (
<figureCitation box="[697,816,1638,1664]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 42" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,474,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[198,1390,474,2057]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 42. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 38 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 39 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 40 — Terminalia, ventral view, 41 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 42 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177240/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[783,816,1638,1664]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus brownish gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,295,1678,1704]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Female.</emphasis>
Body length, 
<number box="[469,519,1678,1704]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.5">10.5</number>
–12.0 mm. Wing length, 7.0–8.0 mm. Thorax and abdomen similar to male. Anterior margin of sternite VIII acuminate, hypogynial valves with seven long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1278,1718,1744]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 42" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,474,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[198,1390,474,2057]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 42. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 38 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 39 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 40 — Terminalia, ventral view, 41 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 42 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177240/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[1245,1278,1718,1744]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with anterior end acuminate, distal apodeme wide (
<figureCitation box="[751,871,1758,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 42" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,474,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[198,1390,474,2057]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 42. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 38 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 39 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 40 — Terminalia, ventral view, 41 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 42 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177240/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[837,871,1758,1784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus two-segmented, distal segment suboval (
<figureCitation box="[159,277,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 42" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[198,1389,474,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[198,1390,474,2057]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 42. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 38 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 39 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 40 — Terminalia, ventral view, 41 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 42 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177240/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[244,277,1798,1824]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="40.0">40</number>
</figureCitation>
); long common spermathecal and spermathecal ducts; spermathecae subovoid (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1327,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,194,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[169,1417,194,1550]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Chrysopilus semipictus sp. n., male holotype: 34 — Wing, 35 — Antenna, 36 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 37 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177239/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figure 
<number box="[1294,1327,1798,1824]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,944,1838,1864]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" box="[197,944,1838,1864]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,1838,1864]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the type-locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,872,1944]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1878,1904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name comes from the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[896,950,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">semi</emphasis>
, for half, and 
<emphasis box="[1114,1184,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">pictus</emphasis>
, for painted, colored, as a reference to the wing pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
